{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9869c41f-d1fd-4eee-8d14-db2a62ed9721","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run `dotnet restore` then `dotnet build` to catch any breaking changes or deprecated APIs. Check the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/) for any breaking changes relevant to your dependencies.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"17b061dd-67bd-4d96-b4ba-4de72d785df8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a general knowledge question - I don't need to look at any files since they described their setup. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":281,"requestId":"A461:3EBA4C:22CD79D:268B505:6A03D924"},"id":"a2229c71-e1e0-4a74-84d5-1f3a4565af92","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:51:39.522Z","parentId":"cce032db-22e9-494f-9ab9-d31a18c429db"}
